{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}} {{BLP sources|date=April 2009}} {{Infobox philosopher | honorific_prefix = | name = Shannon Bell | honorific_suffix = | image = <!-- filename only, i.e. without the File: (or Image:) prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | other_names = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1955|07|05}} | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | nationality = [[Canadians|Canadian]] | religion = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = [[York University]] | notable_works = [https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/6416880 ''Reading, writing and rewriting the prostitute body.'' (Ph.D Thesis)] (1992) | awards = | signature = | signature_size = | signature_alt = | era = | region = | school_tradition = | institutions = [[York University]] | main_interests = [[Experimental philosophy]] | notable_ideas = | influences = | influenced = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Shannon Bell''' (born 5 July 1955) is a Canadian [[performance art|performance]] [[philosopher]] who lives and writes [[Experimental philosophy|philosophy-in-action]], experimental philosophy. Bell is also professor and graduate programme director in the [[York University]] Political Science Department, [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada. She teaches [[postmodern philosophy|postmodern theory]], [[fast feminism]], [[Human sexuality#Society and politics|sexual politics]], [[cyberculture|cyber politics]], [[identity politics]] and [[structural violence|violent philosophy]].
== Research == Bell is currently researching extreme science and art for her book entitled ''Fast Bodies''; this research is funded by [[Social Science and Humanities Research Council]] (SSHRC).
